==Italian==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|it|VL.||essere}}, from {{inh|it|la|esse}}, present active infinitive of {{m|la|sum||I am}}, from {{inh|it|itc-pro|*ezom}}, from {{inh|it|ine-pro|*h₁ésti||I am, I exist}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈɛs.se.re/|[ˈɛs̪ːer̺e]|lang=it}}
* {{audio|It-essere.ogg|Audio|lang=it}}
* {{hyphenation|ès|se|re|lang=it}}

===Verb===
{{it-verb}}

# {{lb|it|intransitive|indicating existence, identity, location, or a permanent quality}} to [[be]]
# {{lb|it|auxiliary|used to form composite past tense of many intransitive verbs}} to have (done something); to [[be]] in the state of having (done something); {{non-gloss definition|See [[:Category:Italian verbs taking essere as auxiliary]].}}
# {{lb|it|impersonal|of a duration of time since an event}} to have [[pass]]ed

====Conjugation====
The present participle ''essente'' is very rare, and is usually replaced with ''stante'', the present participle of ''[[stare]]''. Similarly the past participle ''[[essuto]]'' has disappeared, with ''[[stato]]'', the past participle of ''stare'', being used instead.<ref>[http://dizionari.hoepli.it/Dizionario_Italiano/parola/essuto.aspx?idD=1&Query=essuto&lettera=E]</ref>

